<subSubSection id="9DF36F49B49FC29CE54686B71F091E15" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="6EC355581EC6737A2A773BEFF0D8B42B" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="BC36416B51AB9BA9E5450681A1A5C3DF" authority="Vain" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine minuta" order="Teloschistales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minuta">Pyxine minuta Vain</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DFC0F9F1121F8A7891C7D85EFF68EA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="71342D0DD98AA03DFF89BA8AE472108A" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6248346DF80BBE90EFD47C3C11BB4391" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="4B361B4CEA2705F51E8E6CBA92C0EED4" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine minuta" order="Caliciales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minuta">Pyxine minuta</taxonomicName>
is characterised by narrow lobes, centrally subcrustaceous, saxicolous thalli, a whitish-grey or grey-brown upper surface; brownish-black lower surface with black and simple rhizines, a lack of isidia and soredia and a white or whitish stramineous medulla. Apothecia common, 0.5-1.5 mm wide; internal stipe absent or not distinct. Upper cortex K+ yellowish, UV+ yellow, medulla 
<normalizedToken id="9DDEA4CD1080AF13A2BE229B1FBB9C1D" originalValue="K–">K-</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="09E94A08751AF5A5168EB30D52A858F6" originalValue="C–">C-</normalizedToken>
; containing lichexanthone (major) and terpenoids (detected by TLC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0E6B0CFA4B56246C0F3EA06DBE69B453" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="6D9445D543DA0EF4D05FBD77F443DC3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Habitat and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBE95F12D1716009BDED289C34ECA11B" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
Growing on bark of 
<taxonomicName id="778308421EA0AB9D88BDBA15CB1F2440" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
spp. or rock around 1090-2230 m elevation in semi-arid environments. Worldwide distribution: India (
<bibRefCitation id="328E6CB6EDEF3F93069B02A026305DFD" author="Awasthi, DD" journalOrPublisher="Phytomorphology" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="359 - 379" title="Pyxine in India." volume="30" year="1982">Awasthi 1982</bibRefCitation>
), Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="5D50859B58A7A632346608F1D361D0DC" author="Rogers, RW" journalOrPublisher="Australia Journal of Boany" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="131 - 154" title="The genus Pyxine (Physciaceae, lichenized ascomycetes) in Australia." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/BT9860131" volume="34" year="1986">Rogers 1986</bibRefCitation>
) and newly recorded in China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="939C719C14025F7B769EB6306DEFDFB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5382807E379BF2CB164271B342F33EE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5AC6BD422A1BD6D3885869E326FEB448" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
There is some confusion in the classification of 
<taxonomicName id="329D4B6DC16B9827CD6DB35D9CB00309" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine minuta" order="Caliciales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minuta">Pyxine minuta</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="01CDCAF6D252E952F37D6942DFCCD196" genus="P." lsidName="P. pyxinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="pyxinoides">P. pyxinoides</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="59ED9A6A15B63114D558234342BC0BC8" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine minuta" order="Caliciales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minuta">Pyxine minuta</taxonomicName>
is characterised by narrow lobes, an absent or indistinct internal stipe, small spores (11-16 (18) 
<normalizedToken id="BA9EC97E4FE9772D568ED9267B8886B6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 
<normalizedToken id="E697D8C07051D76EC6AAD3E72AB808E5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and a white medulla. Based on the world key to 
<taxonomicName id="5F5E23BE63E7B618196E52A8EF6EE2FF" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine" order="Caliciales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Pyxine</taxonomicName>
species with lichexanthone (
<bibRefCitation id="448B1A24C3582621632891759E8E3E04" author="Aptroot, A" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="669 - 672" title="A world key to the species of Pyxine with lichexanthone, with a new species from Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282914000231" volume="46" year="2014">Aptroot et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="81667A8A16B22E31D8995EE2758A1F76" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Kalb 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3F1385064E084735CC12E291331CA472" author="Huneck, S" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="331 - 338" title="The chemistry of Dirinaria and Pyxine species (Pyxinaceae) from South America." volume="62" year="1987">Huneck et al. 1987</bibRefCitation>
), the characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="8F8BD928A0ED3E44DE2CE736046D7152" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Pyxine" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pyxine pyxinoides" order="Caliciales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pyxinoides">Pyxine pyxinoides</taxonomicName>
are: Thallus without isidia, pustules or soredia, usually with apothecia; Medulla yellow, ochraceous or salmon; apothecium margin black, not thalline; apothecium without a clear stipe; one TLC run of a portion of the thallus without apothecia showed traces of a substance running like norstictic acid (
<bibRefCitation id="39E1AC0CB0925E8EADDEAE7542AE0F8B" author="Obermayer, W" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Licheologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="247 - 267" title="Notes on three species of Pyxine (Lichenized Ascomycetes) from Tibet and adjacent regions." volume="104" year="2010">Obermayer and Kalb 2010</bibRefCitation>
); neotropical. We did not find any specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="2D62F4E60F68CDEB8F18B47B2445CFBE" genus="P." lsidName="P. pyxinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="pyxinoides">P. pyxinoides</taxonomicName>
in our collections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
